<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1602,2023]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,151,213]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1998,2023]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
The spiny thecal tip and lobate subgenital plates are characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt" authorityName="Schmidt" box="[1108,1388,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Tropidorhinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1284,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Tropidorhinella</emphasis>
Schmidt
</taxonomicName>
, but the styles, pregenital tergal lobes and shape of the pronotum show that these genera are not related. This species is 3% divergent from the lineage to which belongs an undescribed female (also from 
<collectingRegion box="[1078,1162,188,213]" country="Mexico" name="Sinaloa" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">Sinaloa</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1198,1289,188,213]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">
<collectingCountry box="[1198,1289,188,213]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="221">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
